<paragraph id="8BAA431C5C12FFFFFF52FE6FFE87F380" blockId="2.[189,303,477,503]" box="[189,303,477,503]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<heading id="D0E2F4705C12FFFFFF52FE6FFE87F380" bold="true" box="[189,303,477,503]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B9619F0E5C12FFFFFF52FE6FFE87F380" bold="true" box="[189,303,477,503]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA431C5C12FFFEFF52FDBEFDE5F331" blockId="2.[189,1399,524,656]" lastBlockId="3.[189,1400,265,327]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="4" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
We examined the 
<typeStatus id="54AEFDBE5C12FFFFFE7FFDBEFE6BF051" box="[400,451,524,550]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">type</typeStatus>
specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C15389F5C12FFFFFD82FDBEFC70F051" authorityName="Gorochov &amp; Storozhenko" authorityYear="1992" box="[621,984,524,550]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Microtachycines" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tamdaonensis">
<emphasis id="B9619F0E5C12FFFFFD82FDBEFC70F051" box="[621,984,524,550]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Microtachycines tamdaonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in ZIN and discussed with Dr A.V. Gorochov. We are sure that the male tenth abdominal tergite has a large outgrowth in the middle and the male epiproct is semicircular. Moreover, we examined the 
<typeStatus id="54AEFDBE5C12FFFFFC51FDE1FC59F01A" box="[958,1009,595,621]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">type</typeStatus>
specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C15389F5C12FFFFFB4BFDE1FAE9F01B" authorityName="Qin, Liu &amp; Li" authorityYear="2017" box="[1188,1345,594,620]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Megatachycines" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elongatus">
<emphasis id="B9619F0E5C12FFFFFB4BFDE1FAE9F01B" box="[1188,1345,594,620]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">M. elongatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C15389F5C12FFFFFF52FDC4FECCF0F8" authorityName="Qin, Liu &amp; Li" authorityYear="2020" box="[189,356,630,655]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Megatachycines" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trispinosus">
<emphasis id="B9619F0E5C12FFFFFF52FDC4FECCF0F8" box="[189,356,630,655]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">M. trispinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in SEMCAS. All abdominal tergites of the two species have no outgrowths, but they have an extended epiproct. Therefore, we establish a new genus, 
<taxonomicName id="4C15389F5C13FFFEFC6DFEBBFBE9F354" authority="Zhu &amp; Shi &amp; Zhou, 2022" authorityName="Zhu &amp; Shi &amp; Zhou" authorityYear="2022" box="[898,1089,265,291]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Megatachycines" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
